text: An election happened on November 3, 2020 to elect a Senator from the U.S. state of Mississippi. The main two people in the election were Cindy Hyde- Smith (Republican Party) and Mike Espy (Democratic Party). Hyde-Smith won the election and stayed as Senator. Primary elections happened on March 10, 2020. There were three people in the Democratic Party primary: Mike Espy, Tobey Bartee, and Jensen Bohren. Espy won this primary. Only Cindy Hyde-Smith was in the Republican Party primary as she was already a Sneator. The Libertarian Party chose Jimmy Edwards for the election. ==Democratic Party primary== ==Republican Party primary== ===Other candidates=== ====Libertarian Party==== =====Nominee===== *Jimmy Edwards ==Results== ==References== Category:2020 United States Senate elections Category:2020s in Mississippi
title: 2020 United States Senate election in Mississippi
